{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Both models for full participant cohorts and matched cohorts were re-performed in sex strata using the same method based upon sex reported in the UCSF EHR to augment the OMOP database.",
    "Models were trained on two sex subgroups-female and male-due to lack of other subgroups labeled in the EHR.",
    "For each stratum, individuals with AD were re-matched to controls within each stratum for the matched participant trained models.",
    "Models were evaluated similarly based on AUROC/AUPRC on the same bootstrapped held-out evaluation set, stratified by sex.",
    "RF models were investigated for feature interpretation due to the combined interpretable nature of the models (compared to neural networks) and the ability to capture nonlinear relationships (compared to logistic regression models) 95."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
